- cs.CY (Computers and Society): The study focuses on improving clinical interventions and treatments for AKI, which has a significant impact on society and healthcare.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper uses AI techniques to identify AKI sub-phenotypes and improve early prediction of the disease.
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper leverages both structured and unstructured EHR data to identify AKI sub-phenotypes, which involves natural language processing techniques.
- cs.DB (Databases): The study uses a real-world critical care EHR corpus to identify AKI sub-phenotypes, which involves database management and analysis.
